<section class="lifecycle-flow" aria-labelledby="lifecycle-flow-title">
  <div class="lifecycle-flow__header">
    <h2 id="lifecycle-flow-title">Lifecycle Artifact Flow</h2>
    <p>
      Each step leaves evidence for the next step. Gates check that the evidence
      is ready before the workflow moves forward.
    </p>
  </div>

  <ol class="lifecycle-flow__list">
    <li>
      <h3>Idea</h3>
      <p>Problem, request, support note, or transcript.</p>
      <span>Input</span>
    </li>
    <li>
      <h3>PRD</h3>
      <p>Requirements, success criteria, and SPEC catalog.</p>
      <span>Product artifact</span>
    </li>
    <li>
      <h3>Roadmap</h3>
      <p>SPEC-ID, dependencies, status, and execution order.</p>
      <span>Planning artifact</span>
    </li>
    <li>
      <h3>Scaffold</h3>
      <p>Workflow file, design concept, spec folder, and MOC.</p>
      <span>Setup gate</span>
    </li>
    <li>
      <h3>Specify</h3>
      <p>User stories and functional requirements in <code>spec.md</code>.</p>
      <span>G1</span>
    </li>
    <li>
      <h3>Clarify</h3>
      <p>Open questions resolved before planning starts.</p>
      <span>G2</span>
    </li>
    <li>
      <h3>Plan</h3>
      <p>Implementation approach, contracts, research, and quickstart.</p>
      <span>G3</span>
    </li>
    <li>
      <h3>Checklist</h3>
      <p>UX, accessibility, integration, and error-handling gaps.</p>
      <span>G4</span>
    </li>
    <li>
      <h3>Tasks</h3>
      <p>Reviewable work items grouped by user story.</p>
      <span>G5</span>
    </li>
    <li>
      <h3>Analyze</h3>
      <p>Cross-artifact drift review before implementation.</p>
      <span>G6</span>
    </li>
    <li>
      <h3>Implement</h3>
      <p>Docs changes, validation evidence, and PR packet.</p>
      <span>G7</span>
    </li>
  </ol>
</section>

